Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags.

lardataobj builds with DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR. GCC 14's new -Wtemplate-body
diagnostic flags Utilities/BitMask.tcc:226 (`bits.negate()` — a member visible
only later in the header) and WERROR promotes the warning to a hard error:

  BitMask.tcc:226:24: error: '... Bits_t<Storage>::This_t ...' has no member
  named 'negate' [-Wtemplate-body]

The code is correct on the reference compiler; this is a newer-GCC diagnostic.
CXXFLAGS can't demote it (cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror) lands after
$CXXFLAGS), so drop the WERROR keyword. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -17,7 +17,6 @@ cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic -Wno-unused-local-typedefs
 )
